         <abstract id="aspace_1506cd245d2d19067e47a1ddbf1c43a1">Translations and notes on the texts of Latin and Greek classics; essays on classical authors, and a few pieces of correspondence and poetry. Included are some poems and letters in connection with Mikhail Rostovtsev's sixtieth birthday.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n85237420" source="naf">
               <part>Mendell, Clarence W. (Clarence Whittlesey), 1883-1970</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_b773176f0248325ab19710e0db91b83c">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Gift of Mrs. Clarence Mendell, 1971, and Lewis S. Welch, 1941.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_39d2457f80ecfd597d2290649a7fa084">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_202dd30fcf3d023973b28c0953212544">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Clarence Whittlesey Mendell Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_e8263a52ad8ba93aecfd68baa9a63638">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Clarence W. Mendell was professor of Latin and Greek from 1911-1952 at Yale University, and was professor emeritus from 1952-1963.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_50adefa9f7281eba7e111a3c3b7a37af">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Translations and notes on the texts of Latin and Greek classics; essays on classical authors, and a few pieces of correspondence and poetry. Included are some poems and letters in connection with Mikhail Rostovtsev's sixtieth birthday.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
